				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="リトルレギオン (Little Legion)" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#170;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#136;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#171;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#172;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#174;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#170;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#179; (Little Legion) is a two player card game from Japan. Players build a tableau of three cards in three columns (similar to games like Battle Line). Likewise, players are building scoring combos to claim the different keys as prizes.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The deck has 35 cards, from 1 to 7 in five colours.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each round, 3 fresh keys are drawn from a bag and placed as a line between the players. The deck is shuffled, and five cards are dealt face-up alongside the keys. Each player is dealt three hand cards, and gets a player aid showing the possible combos.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On their turn, a player draws a card and then plays a card to the tableau, or discards and pulls a face-up card to the tableau instead. Whenever a player completes a column on three cards, they draw one more card and discard from their hand.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Cards can be played face-down to a column. A player can discard two cards, and use a discard from the other players side instead.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When the three keys have three cards set on both sides, any face-down cards are turned up. Equal combos do not get a key, otherwise the winning combo claims a key.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The deck is shuffled over for the next round and fresh keys are pulled from the bag to make up the line.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Play continues until one player wins enough keys.&amp;#10;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
